    <item>
      <title>Re: Caster specific Augs</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=180662#M180662</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Naubi wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;A better question to ask would be why they didnt give the melee epics an innate proc. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Would you rather the casters epics had no foci, but had two augs slots to give you the option of putting DoN foci augs in them?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Message Edited by Naubi on &lt;SPAN class=date_text&gt;02-08-2006&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;SPAN class=time_text&gt;08:28 PM&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;At the time we did the epics, items could only hold 1 spell (worn, activated, or proc) and one focus effect. However, sometime shortly after Omens launch, we changed the system for items that have spells on them, to allow an item to carry multiple spells (multiple worn or multiple procs, and an activated) and to allow for multiple foci on an item. This led to us revising the effect on the necromancer epic, so that they were allowed a worn spell (their worn effect is not a focus, fyi) and a clickie spell on the same item.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We could have gone back and removed the type 4 augment from all epics and added a proc, however, at the time, I felt that it wouldn't gain us any approval from players since most of the players with either a 1.5 or 2.0 already had their type4 slot augmented. Moreover, we would have had to make unique 'epic' style procs for the weapons, which I imagine would have garnered complaints from casters for losing a type4 slot, as well as seeing their melee counterparts "compensated" for it with a proc.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It was a sticky situation, and that's why epics are what they are right now. I still don't approve of some of the bigger, more powerful augments being type all (like the BiC and others) since there are items I want to create that use a specific set of augments, but can't, since the type-alls can go into any set and throw off the intentions of that set. It was never really intended for an epic to have more than 500 hps or mana, making it very hard to replace for a good many expansions.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
