&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I had considered doing this before the DoN armor type9 augment additions. Consider if I had did it back then; augments like the BiC wouldn't fit in type 9, 11, or 12. I would wager that as soon as a new augment slot went in (such as the type 9s in DoN or the 12s for tradeskills) I would have gotten requests/complaints that the functionality of their previous 'type all' BiC augment now won't fit in these new slots. Now, I could still change them to work with all slot types we've currently been using (including 9 and 12), but the negative feedback on the handful or so type-all augments will be a lot bigger than what you'd expect, especially when new slot types are introduced&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
